2. PATTERN ATTRIBUTION
================================================================================

LLM Wiki pattern (3-layer raw / wiki / schema)
- Original idea by Andrej Karpathy, described publicly at
  https://gist.github.com/karpathy/442a6bf555914893e9891c11519de94f (2026)
- Sillok is an independent productized implementation of the publicly
  described pattern. Per 17 U.S.C. §102(b), ideas, methods, and systems
  are not subject to copyright protection. Sillok extends the pattern
  with a typed pack registry, two-stage routing, proposal-only governance,
  and multi-tenant overlays — none of which are part of Karpathy's gist.

Memex (1945)
- Vannevar Bush's "As We May Think" (Atlantic Monthly, July 1945) — public
  domain by virtue of authorship and publication date.

Zettelkasten
- Niklas Luhmann's slip-box methodology (1960s) and its modern English
  treatment by Sönke Ahrens, "How to Take Smart Notes" (2017) — referenced
  for comparative purposes only; no text reproduction.

